NO CONTEST plea entered to the charge of disorderly conduct.  Convicted.
Sentence is withheld and the defendant is placed on probation to DOC for twelve (12) months.
Conditions of probation:
1) assessment, treatment, counseling as deemed appropriate by the Department's assessment process;
2) maintain fulltime employment, schooling or combination, if defendant is physically and emotionally able to work;
3) spend ten (10) days in the county jail, under the Huber Law, stayed and to be imposed at the agent's discretion and upon order of the court;
4) maintain absolute sobriety;
5) no contact with Christopher Lemberger or Verian Martinez;
6) provide DNA sample and pay the surcharge;
7) pay court costs (apply $150.00 cash bail);
8) pay supervision fees in an amount to be determined by DOC.
Minutes.
